main event: A ground-radar sighting of a metallic, disc-shaped object without lights over Big Pine Key, Florida on June 23, 1964.
interesting points: The object was high in the sky and moving steadily under apparent artificial control.
The sighting was reported to the Department of the Air Force and several military organizations.
The object was described as larger than a DC-3 twin-engine high-wing aircraft.
The sighting occurred at around 11:55 PM and was observed for an unspecified length of time.
The object was sighted by a witness named Mr. Big Pine Key, Florida.
sighted object: a metallic, disc-shaped object without lights
